headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 31 points, Dyson Daniels added 22 points, seven rebounds and seven assists and the Atlanta Hawks clobbered the short-handed Charlotte Hornets 134-102 on Tuesday night to sweep the four-game season series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trae Young scores 31 as Hawks rout Hornets 134-102 to sweep 4-game season series

headlines.description: — Baylor Scheierman scored 13 of his career-high 20 points in the fourth quarter, Kristaps Porzingis had 25 points and 13 rebounds and the Boston Celtics beat the Brooklyn Nets 104-96 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Baylor Scheierman and Kristaps Porzingis lead the Celtics to a 104-96 win over the Nets

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler had 24 points, eight rebounds and 10 assists and the Golden State Warriors, playing without Stephen Curry, beat the Milwaukee Bucks 104-93 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler scores 24 and Warriors win without Curry, 104-93 over Bucks

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 33 points and the Los Angeles Clippers handed the East-leading Cleveland Cavaliers their second straight loss, 132-119 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers rally past Cavaliers 132-119, handing East leaders a second straight loss
